div.p:
(1) A temptation of the appetite or passion;

(2) A yielding to pride, fashion, or vanity;

(3) A desire for worldly riches or power and dominion over lands or earthly possessions of
men.

"Like the man who faces what he must

    With step triumphant and a heart of cheer;

    Who fights the daily battle without fear;

    Sees his hopes fail, yet keeps unfaltering trust

    That God is God."

"The world wants men—true men

    Who cannot be bought or sold;

    Men who will scorn to violate truth—genuine gold."
